<item>
            <title>[LU-16990] Use NETWORK_TIMEOUT message status for TN_EVENT_TAG_RX_CANCEL</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16990</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I noticed that after the MDS hit Inbound wait, it was failing transactions with REMOTE_TIMEOUT health status:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
[Wed Mar  8 11:26:29 2023] LNet: 143125:0:(lib-msg.c:814:lnet_health_check()) Message from 17@kfi to 0@kfi exceeded message deadline by 2 seconds rc=-110 hstatus=REMOTE_TIMEOUT
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Comes from this code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
static int kfilnd_tn_state_wait_timeout_tag_comp(struct kfilnd_transaction *tn,
                                                 enum tn_events event,
                                                 int status, bool *tn_released)
{
        KFILND_TN_DEBUG(tn, &quot;%s event status %d&quot;, tn_event_to_str(event),
                        status);

        switch (event) {
        case TN_EVENT_TAG_RX_CANCEL:
                kfilnd_tn_status_update(tn, -ETIMEDOUT,
                                        LNET_MSG_STATUS_REMOTE_TIMEOUT);
                kfilnd_peer_tn_failed(tn-&amp;gt;tn_kp, -ETIMEDOUT);
                break;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Current behavior means that the server never realizes its local NIC is not healthy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[root@s-lmo-gaz38a ~]# lnetctl net show -v 2 | grep -e nid -e health
        - nid: 0@lo
          health stats:
              health value: 1000
        - nid: 172.18.2.3@tcp
          health stats:
              health value: 1000
        - nid: 17@kfi
          health stats:
              health value: 1000
[root@s-lmo-gaz38a ~]#
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
